    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-01T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1044A</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-01T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2039. Department appreciates gravity of the political situation and the possible
                    danger of a crisis. Do you recommend any moderation of Department’s attitude
                    towards the Bolsheviki authorities? If so, explicitly state your views.
                    Department is not disposed to put you and the members of the Embassy staff in
                    personal danger if it can be avoided without compromising the position of the
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
